# Premiere CEP Extension Context

Read `premiere-extension/KEYBOARD_SHORTCUTS.md` for detailed research on how
keyboard shortcuts work (and don't work) in Premiere Pro CEP extensions.

## Key facts

- `registerKeyEventsInterest` uses **macOS native keyCodes (0–127)**, not DOM keyCodes
- Register ALL keyCodes 0–127 on panel load so the panel receives key events
- Only single keys work (no Cmd/Ctrl/Shift combos on macOS)
- Raw `__adobe_cep__.addEventListener` expects a **string** callback, not a function ref
- `closeExtension()` has known bugs — avoid it; keep panels alive
- Cross-panel communication (CSXS events, localStorage) is unreliable in Premiere
- Headless trigger panels should be self-contained (read settings, find file, call JSX directly)
- Global shortcuts use macOS App Shortcuts mapped to menu items from headless Panel-type extensions
- Headless panels auto-start via `<StartOn><Event>applicationActivate</Event></StartOn>`

## Architecture

- `main.js` — main panel: file list, settings, panel shortcuts via registerAllKeys()
- `import_headless.html` / `insert_headless.html` — self-contained trigger panels
- `premiere.jsx` — ExtendScript (importAndPlace, importOnly, browseForFolder, etc.)
- `CSXS/manifest.xml` — 3 extensions: main panel + 2 headless triggers
- `install.sh` — deploys to `~/Library/Application Support/Adobe/CEP/extensions/`

## Current status

- Panel shortcuts (focused): WORKING — single keys and F-keys
- Global shortcuts: headless panel opens on macOS App Shortcut trigger, but the
  action may not execute — focus/visibilitychange events need investigation
